transcript.text: Hello, welcome to on print shop.
This video is about store inventory management.
So in this video we will see inventory option will allow private store customer to place orders with large printing quantity when they don't want all printing quantities to be shipped at one time.
Private store customer can raise the request for required product quantity as per their needs from available product quantity in order.
So let's see how it works in admin or how we can configure it in admin.
Just go to the admin, then go to store management stores.
So we can set inventory on the basis of product.
Just click on action, go to the configuration.
Here you can see the inventory.
So here for the assigned products, we can set inventories.

So if any of customer who will place orders either of 2500 quantities or more than 2500 quantities then he can activate or he can ask for the inventory option where the minimum shipping quantity would be 1000 cost per unit print.
Like if the 1000 cards are shipped out of 2500 then 1500 cards will be remaining and the storage charges for 1500 cards is 0.01 dollar per unit cost.
Then shipment handling cost.
Let's say if a customer asks shipping two or three times then each time he has to pay the shipping handling cost then storage days will be 90 days.
So this inventory will be automatically discarded after the 90 days.
Now you can just click on save.
So that's how you can manage an inventory for a business card.
Let's see how it works at a front end or how the customer places an order and how exactly it works.
So here we are on the product where customer can select a business card, click on Customize button, click on continue.
If you see the 100 quantities, if you will click on inventory, yes, the system will not allow because the minimum 2500 printing quantity must be needed.
Now if you select 2500 quantities then the inventory option will work OK.
So you can see from 2500 quantities, you can ask for minimum shipment quantities 1000 and handling cost will be $15.00.
So here you can see the total cost is $55.99.
You can just tick on terms and condition and click on save and add to cart.
So here you can see and you can just make the payment order will be placed as you will click on complete order and if you click on view details you can see it.
So here you can see the inventory, let's say out of 2501 thousand quantity has placed order and 1500 are remaining.
So whenever next time customer wants he can just come on the same page and click on continue button and he can ask for the remaining quantities.
At the same time if you go in admin side.
So in the admin, the inventory is also mentioned over here at this page, the printer can see where and at which time he has asked for the remaining quantities.
So this is the way you can manage the inventories.
If you have any queries, please connect with us at support onprintshop.com.
Thank you.
